  "text": "As indicated above, in bands 7e9 of CN-PAGE, peptides from FNR (PetH) were identified with best confidence values at band 8 (Table 3) . In these bands, the following components of cytochrome b 6 f complex, b 6 (PetB), f (PetA) and Rieske protein (PetC) were also identified (Tables 2, 3 , and 4). We analyzed in silico the amino acid sequence N-terminal of FNR from Prochlorococcus MED4 [CITATION_1] , which has a segment that predicts a transmembrane helix (Suppl. Fig. 2b ). This predicted transmembrane helix was found in 9 more species of Prochlorococcus (Suppl. Table 6 . Proteomic identification of PSII subunits in the sucrose gradient fractions separated (Fig. 3a) . Analysis of the fractions by SDS-PAGE (Fig. 3b*) . Fig 2e) .",
